Wow, I have been following this thread for awhile and it seems like the
princess and the pea syndrome. I didn't think that most people were that
sensitive to a 1/8" adjustment. As far as the rear goes, you only have
up and down adjustment with your swingarm. When I restored the proper
height on my truck I had to make sure I was on a level floor first and
that my frame was level before I adjusted the swingarms.

